#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:446
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Any init script <e>requires</e> the <c>start()</c> function to be defined. All\n"
"other sections are optional.\n"
msgstr "initスクリプトでは<c>start()</c>関数が定義されていることが<e>必須</e>です。他のすべてのセクションは、定義してもしなくてもよいです。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:453
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Dependencies"
msgstr "依存関係"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:457
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There are two dependency-alike settings you can define that influence the\n"
"start-up or sequencing of init scripts: <c>use</c> and <c>need</c>. Next to\n"
"these two, there are also two order-influencing methods called <c>before</c> and\n"
"<c>after</c>. These last two are no dependencies per se - they do not make the\n"
"original init script fail if the selected one isn't scheduled to start (or fails\n"
"to start).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:467
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The <c>use</c> settings informs the init system that this script <e>uses</e>\n"
"    functionality offered by the selected script, but does not directly depend\n"
"    on it. A good example would be <c>use logger</c> or <c>use dns</c>. If those\n"
"    services are available, they will be put in good use, but if you do not have\n"
"    a logger or DNS server the services will still work. If the services exist,\n"
"    then they are started before the script that <c>use</c>'s them.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:475
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The <c>need</c> setting is a hard dependency. It means that the script that\n"
"    is <c>need</c>'ing another script will not start before the other script is\n"
"    launched successfully. Also, if that other script is restarted, then this\n"
"    one will be restarted as well.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:481
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    When using <c>before</c>, then the given script is launched before the\n"
"    selected one <e>if</e> the selected one is part of the init level. So an\n"
"    init script <path>xdm</path> that defines <c>before alsasound</c> will start\n"
"    before the <path>alsasound</path> script, but only if <path>alsasound</path>\n"
"    is scheduled to start as well in the same init level. If\n"
"    <path>alsasound</path> is not scheduled to start too, then this particular\n"
"    setting has no effect and <path>xdm</path> will be started when the init\n"
"    system deems it most appropriate.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:491
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Similarly, <c>after</c> informs the init system that the given script should\n"
"    be launched after the selected one <e>if</e> the selected one is part of the\n"
"    init level. If not, then the setting has no effect and the script will be\n"
"    launched by the init system when it deems it most appropriate.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:499
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"It should be clear from the above that <c>need</c> is the only \"true\" dependency\n"
"setting as it affects if the script will be started or not. All the others are\n"
"merely pointers towards the init system to clarify in which order scripts can be\n"
"(or should be) launched.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:506
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now, if you look at many of Gentoo's available init scripts, you will notice\n"
"that some have dependencies on things that are no init scripts. These \"things\"\n"
"we call <e>virtuals</e>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:512
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A <e>virtual</e> dependency is a dependency that a service provides, but that is\n"
"not provided solely by that service. Your init script can depend on a system\n"
"logger, but there are many system loggers available (metalogd, syslog-ng,\n"
"sysklogd, ...). As you cannot <c>need</c> every single one of them (no sensible\n"
"system has all these system loggers installed and running) we made sure that\n"
"all these services <c>provide</c> a virtual dependency.\n"
msgstr "<e>virtual</e>依存とは、あるサービスが提供する依存関係ですが、そのサービスだけが提供するものではありません。たとえば、あるinitスクリプトがシステムロガーに依存するとします。しかし、たくさんのシステムロガー(metalogd、syslog-ng、sysklogd等々)が存在しているので、その中の一つのシステムロガーだけに<c>need</c>依存することはできません(また、すべてのシステムロガーをインストールして、実行することのもナンセンスです)。このような場合、すべてのシステムロガーがvirutal依存関係を<c>provide(提供)</c>するようにします。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
