#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:558
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Controlling the Order"
msgstr "順番の制御"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:562
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As we described in the previous section, you can tell the init system what order\n"
"it should use for starting (or stopping) scripts. This ordering is handled both\n"
"through the dependency settings <c>use</c> and <c>need</c>, but also through the\n"
"order settings <c>before</c> and <c>after</c>. As we have described these\n"
"earlier already, let's take a look at the Portmap service as an example of such\n"
"init script.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:570
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "The depend() function in the Portmap service"
msgstr "portmapサービスのdepend()関数"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:571
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"depend() {\n"
"  need net\n"
"  before inetd\n"
"  before xinetd\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"depend() {\n"
"  need net\n"
"  before inetd\n"
"  before xinetd\n"
"}\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:579
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can also use the \"*\" glob to catch all services in the same runlevel,\n"
"although this isn't advisable.\n"
msgstr "お勧めはしませんが、同一ランレベルのすべてのサービスにあてはまる\"*\"を使用することもできます。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:583
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Running an init script as first script in the runlevel"
msgstr "ランレベル内の最初のスクリプトとしてこのinitスクリプトを実行する"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:584
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"depend() {\n"
"  before *\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"depend() {\n"
"  before *\n"
"}\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:590
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your service must write to local disks, it should need <c>localmount</c>. If\n"
"it places anything in <path>/var/run</path> such as a pidfile, then it should\n"
"start after <c>bootmisc</c>:\n"
msgstr ""
"もし、サービスがローカルディスクに書き込みをしなければならないものであれば、\n"
"<c>localmount</c>が必要となります。\n"
"もし、<path>/var/run</path> にpidファイルのように何か書き込むのであれば、\n"
"<c>bootmisc</c>のあとに開始されなければいけません。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:595
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Example depend() function"
msgstr "Example depend() function"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:596
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"depend() {\n"
"  need localmount\n"
"  after bootmisc\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"depend() {\n"
"  need localmount\n"
"  after bootmisc\n"
"}\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:605
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Standard Functions"
msgstr "標準関数"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:609
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Next to the <c>depend()</c> functionality, you also need to define the\n"
"<c>start()</c> function. This one contains all the commands necessary to\n"
"initialize your service. It is advisable to use the <c>ebegin</c> and\n"
"<c>eend</c> functions to inform the user about what is happening:\n"
msgstr ""
"<c>depend()</c>関数の次に、さらに<c>start()</c>関数を定義する必要があります。\n"
"この関数には、あなたのサービスを初期化するために必要なすべてのコマンドを入れます。何がなされているかをユーザに知らせるために、以下のように<c>ebegin</c>と<c>eend</c>関数を使用することが望ましいです。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:615
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Example start() function"
msgstr "start()関数の例"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:616
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"start() {\n"
"  if [ \"${RC_CMD}\" = \"restart\" ];\n"
"  then\n"
"    <comment># Do something in case a restart requires more than stop, start</comment>\n"
"  fi\n"
"\n"
"  ebegin \"Starting my_service\"\n"
"  start-stop-daemon --start --exec /path/to/my_service \\\n"
"    --pidfile /path/to/my_pidfile\n"
"  eend $?\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"start() {\n"
"  ebegin \"Starting my_service\"\n"
"  start-stop-daemon --start --exec /path/to/my_service \\\n"
"     --pidfile /path/to/my_pidfile\n"
"\n"
"  eend $?\n"
"}\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:630
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Both <c>--exec</c> and <c>--pidfile</c> should be used in start and stop\n"
"functions. If the service does not create a pidfile, then use\n"
"<c>--make-pidfile</c> if possible, though you should test this to be sure.\n"
"Otherwise, don't use pidfiles. You can also add <c>--quiet</c> to the\n"
"<c>start-stop-daemon</c> options, but this is not recommended unless the\n"
"service is extremely verbose.  Using <c>--quiet</c> may hinder debugging if the\n"
"service fails to start.\n"
msgstr ""
"<c>--exec</c> と <c>--pidfile</c> の両方がstart, stop関数のなかで必要です。\n"
"もしサービスがpidファイルを作らないならば、\n"
"できる限り<c>--make-pidfile</c>を使ってください。\n"
"ただし、テストをして確認してください。\n"
"そうでなければ、pidファイルを使用しないでください。\n"
"<c>--quiet</c>を<c>start-stop-daemon</c>オプションに加えることもできますが、\n"
"これは、サービスがかなり冗長なメッセージを出さない限りおすすめできません。\n"
"<c>--quiet</c>を使うことで、サービス開始に失敗した際のデバッグが困難になるかもしれません。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:640
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Another notable setting used in the above example is to check the contents of\n"
"the <c>RC_CMD</c> variable. Unlike the previous init script system, the newer\n"
"<c>openrc</c> system does not support script-specific restart functionality.\n"
"Instead, the script needs to check the contents of the <c>RC_CMD</c> variable\n"
"to see if a function (be it <c>start()</c> or <c>stop()</c>) is called as part\n"
"of a restart or not.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><note>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:649
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Make sure that <c>--exec</c> actually calls a service and not just a shell\n"
"script that launches services and exits -- that's what the init script is\n"
"supposed to do.\n"
msgstr "<c>--exec</c> が、サービスを呼び出したり停止するシェルスクリプトではなく（これはinitスクリプトがサポートする事柄です）、実際にサービスを呼び出すようにしてください。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:655
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you need more examples of the <c>start()</c> function, please read the\n"
"source code of the available init scripts in your <path>/etc/init.d</path>\n"
"directory.\n"
msgstr "<c>start()</c>関数のより多くの例が必要なら、/etc/init.dディレクトリにある利用可能なinitスクリプトのソースコードを見てください。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:661
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Another function you can define is <c>stop()</c>. You are not obliged to define\n"
"this function though! Our init system is intelligent enough to fill in this\n"
"function by itself if you use <c>start-stop-daemon</c>.\n"
msgstr ""
"定義可能な他の関数には、<c>stop()</c>と<c>restart()</c>があります。\n"
"これらの関数を定義することは強制されません! Gentooのinitシステムは、<c>start-stop-daemon</c>を使用する場合には、自動的にinitシステム自身がこれらの関数を適切に処理します。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:667
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Here is an example of a <c>stop()</c> function:\n"
msgstr "stop()関数の例"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-working-rcscripts.xml:670
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Example stop() function"
